1. What is Drag and Drop in Selenium?
- Drag and Dran is an mouse interaction where we drag an element (source) and drop it onto another element (target) using selenium automation

2. Which class is used to perform Drag and Drop?
- We use the ActionChains class from selenium.webdriver.common.action_chains

3. What is the syntax for Drag and Drop?
- Syntax
    ActionChains(driver).drag_and_drop(source, target).perform()

4. Why does drag_and_drop() sometimes fail?
- It may fail because:
    - Element not visible or not interactable
    - Element is inside an iframe
    - Timing issue (page not loaded)
    - Modern UI frameworks (React, Angular) handle events differently

5. What is the alternative approach for Drag and Drop?
- Syntax
    ActionChains(driver).click_and_hold(source)\
                        .move_to_element(target)\
                        .release()\
                        .perform()
-> This is more reliable in real-time application

6. What are different types of Drag and Drop?
- Element to Element
- Drag By Offset(x, y coordinates)

7. How do you perform Drag and Drop by offset?
- Syntax:
    ActionChains(driver).drag_and_drop_by_offset(source , x , y).peform()

8. How do you handle Drag and Drop inside an iframe?
- First switch to iframe
    driver.switch_to_iframe("frame_name")
- Then perform drag and perform

9. Drag and Drop is not working. What will you do?
- Check if element is visible
- Add explicit wait
- Check for iframe and switch
- Try alternative method (click_and_wait)
- Use Javascript executor if needed

10. Can we use JavaScript for Drag and Drop?
- YES , when selenium actions fail (especially in complex UI apps), we can use Javascript executor to simulate drag and drop events.

11. What is perform() in ActionChains?
- perform() executes all the actions that are stored in the ActionChains object.

12. What happens if we don’t use perform()?
- The actions will not execute because ActionChains only stores actions until perform() is called.

13. How do you debug Drag and Drop failures?
- Add wait and logs
- Check locators
- Verify element visibily
- Try step-by-step actions
- Use browser developer tools

14. Can Drag and Drop work on all browsers?
- Mostly YES, but behavior may vary slightly depending on browser and application in implementation

